From Blackdog:
THIS WILL NOT FIT THE SMITH AND WESSON RIFLE ALSO KNOWN AS THE S&W.22 LR.

Features: Built with an interchangeable feed tower. You can easily disassemble the drum, slide your AR-22 tower out and replace it with the new Black Dog 10-22 or S&W.22 feed towers.

Material: Polycarbonate & Glass Filled Nylon

We do not guarantee that the drum will work in full-auto setups.  However, many customers report that with a little fine tuning they can get the drum to work in full-auto.

Compatible conversion units :

    Ciener/Atchisson

    Tactical Solutions
    Target Master
    Kel-Tec PLR22
    Sig Sauer 522

Recommended Ammunition: Federal, CCI/Blazer, American Eagle. Use a round nosed bullet. Stay away from hollow points. Ammunition not listed will not feed well in our products.



Black dummy rounds: The plastic black dummy rounds are an important part of the drum assembly. They feed the ammo from the drum body to the tower. BDM does not recommend using dummy rounds as real bullets.

Clear rubber bands: Each drum is assembled with one clear rubber band and two extra bands taped to the inside of the drum box.

Spring Tension: If you come across feeding issues, the drum spring may be too tight causing ammo to rush up and out the tower. You may also have feeding issues if the spring is too loose. Spring tension may also be required to adjust to your rifle’s bolt speed. The manual provided will guide you through disassembly & assembly. The manual is also available as a PDF on our website.

Winding Rotor: Pulling the rotor counter clockwise and letting go will most likely damage the drum.  It can cause the internal followers to break.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Troy-Bilt Bronco 19hp Kohler 42" cut riding mower
postcontent: This Troy-Bilt Bronco is an outstanding and user friendly riding mower. It has The 19hp Kohler motor in it that runs smooth and strong, giving you plenty of power to cut even tall grass without a problem. The automatic transmission is very user friendly and operates by  the push of a pedal (on the right side) much like a car's throttle pedal.  The brakes (the pedal on the left side of the mower) work good and are independent of the clutch and throttle like other riding mowers with the auto transmission. Giving the operator much more control in tight corners or hills etc.. There is also a brake lock on the dash for parking on hills or trailers or whatever the circumstance may be.  The 42" cut mowing deck  is easy to maintain and if needed, to take off for changing belts. It is controlled by the two levers on the right side of the seat, one controlling the height of the deck and one that turns the blades on and off. The larger discharge shoot that this model has helps reduce any grass clumping that may occur in wet grass. It also has turf saving wheels on the deck. The frame is a fully welded step through model that is very easy to get on and off of and it even has a cup holder (awesome).  Next to the cup holder is the shifter for forward, neutral and reverse. The throttle control on the dash works properly and has full movement. all the way down is for low idle which this mower, at the low idle, runs smooth and quiet. Move the throttle up and you can feel the power of the 19hp engine as it climbs a big hill or attacks the tall grass. All the way up on the throttle is the choke for cold starts but I've found I rarely have to use it. It has an easy to grip wide steering wheel that smoothly turns on a dime. The wide leather seat is very comfortable and is not scratched or torn. This mower was bought new in May and has maybe 15 hours of easy grass time. I have had no problems out of it other than having to put a deck belt on it when a small stick was lodged in between the pulley and made the belt break. A really easy 20 minute fix and I didn't even have to take the deck off. I unplugged the safety switch that shuts the mower off if you try to mow in reverse. This was aggravating if I had to turn around or something while mowing but it can easily be plugged back up for whatever reason if the buyer wishes to. I apologize for the bad pictures. I had just finished mowing when these were taken and it had turned dark outside. I regret having to sell this incredible lawn mower but sometimes life demands sacrifices. feel free to email me any questions or for more pics etc.. thanks
